Adding MultiTap support for the physical keyboard There is a special use-case, which requires a special user-experience:
When the same character is repeating in the sequence (e.g., QQ), the user
is expecting that the output will be cyclular, unlike when the the sequence

Moved cycle handling to the state machine to allow splitting of cycling key sequences. Added initialization of the state machine without active NFAPart. Increased MAX_NFA_DIVIDES to 30, which allows more complex key cycling sequences.

Added new key sequence notification, based on a nondeterministic finite-state machine. Now SHIFT and ALT sequences works correct event with sequences of
more than two keys, even with caps lock.

It's sufficient to use a NFA, as the character sequences are very limited
and the splitting of the NFA small.
